    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="582" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d582">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d582fn1">Printed on <ref target="#pg_1332">page 1332</ref>.</note> received last night
                            regarding Lenz and missionary protection indicates a better spirit on
                            the part of the Turkish Government than your preceding telegram showed,
                            and suggests that good management may avert proposed formal demand for
                            passports. Firmly impress upon Turkish Government our right to be
                            promptly answered as to just demands, and our confidence that the
                            answers will be satisfactory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
